location.RespondingFDTransportInd, location.NBApprovedInd, location.ThousandFeetFireHydrantInd, location.ProofOfPaymentDuesInd, location.LegalDescFormat, location.DisplayProtectionClass, location.ProtectionId, location.ProtectionClass2, location.isUnlisted, location.UWFlag01, location.UWFlag02, location.UWFlag03, location.UWFlag04, location.LocationGeoSelected, location.SelectedProtectionClass, location.PrimaryMeridian, location.GeoCodeCounty, location.AllowPLSSDirty, location.Zone, location.LocationCounterNumber, location.WindHailDeductible, location.UnderlyingPolicyInd, location.PolicyLoadError, location.UnderlyingPolicyLoadedInd, location.UnderlyingQuoteOrAppInd, location.ExcludedInd, location.UnderlyingUMUIMPerPersonLimit, location.UnderlyingUMUIMOccurenceLimit, location.UnderlyingUMUIMCSLOccLimit, location.UnderlyingCombinedSingleLimit, location.UnderlyingLiabilityLimit, location.UnderlyingLimitType, FROM

where systemid in (select SystemId from advrxxchangedbeans where concat(adddt,addtm)>='$$m_strtdt' and concat(adddt,addtm) <='$$m_Enddt' and
 cmmcontainer='Policy') and location.cmmcontainer='Policy'

transformations.description: This reusable expression will properly check and format up to 5 dates that may be in the 'YY-MM-DD' format. It assumes that any years before '50 are in the current century, and any years after '50 are in the previous century.
transformations.name: Exp_format_dates

fields.name: out_Date1
fields.expression:
IIF(ISNULL(in_Date1), NULL,
IIF(SUBSTR(v_Date1, 0, 2) = '00', 
IIF(SUBSTR(v_Date1, 3, 2) <= '50', TO_DATE(SUBSTR(v_Date1, 3), 'YY-MM-DD'), TO_DATE('19' || SUBSTR(v_Date1, 3), 'YYYY-MM-DD')),
IIF(IS_DATE(v_Date1, 'YYYY-MM-DD') and DATE_COMPARE(in_Date1, TO_DATE('1900-01-01', 'YYYY-MM-DD')) > 0 , in_Date1, TO_DATE('1900-01-01', 'YYYY-MM-DD'))))

fields.name: out_Date2
fields.expression:
IIF(ISNULL(in_Date2), NULL,
IIF(SUBSTR(v_Date2, 0, 2) = '00',
